[[File:Ushinsky.jpg|thumb]]
'''康斯坦丁·乌申斯基'''（{{lang-ru|'''Константин Дмитриевич Ушинский'''}}，{{OldStyleDate|1824年|3月2日|2月19日}}-{{OldStyleDate|1871年|1月3日|1870年12月22日}}）是一位[[俄国|俄国]]教育家，俄国科学[[教育学|教育学]]的创建者<ref name=Brockhaus>[http://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/brokgauz/21746 ''Ushinsky'' article] {{Wayback|url=http://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/brokgauz/21746 |date=20160511112155 }} in [[Brockhaus_and_Efron_Encyclopedic_Dictionary|Brockhaus and Efron Encyclopedic Dictionary]] {{ru icon}}</ref> <ref name=bse>[http://www.cultinfo.ru/fulltext/1/001/008/114/995.htm ''Ushinsky'' article] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20050526191953/http://www.cultinfo.ru/fulltext/1/001/008/114/995.htm |date=2005-05-26 }} by [[Eduard_Dneprov|Eduard Dneprov]] in ''[[Great_Soviet_Encyclopedia|Great Soviet Encyclopedia]]'' {{ru icon}}</ref>. 

==生平==

{{OldStyleDate|1824年|3月2日|2月19日}}，康斯坦丁·乌申斯基出生在[[图拉|图拉]]市的一个退休陆军[[中校|中校]]D.K. 乌申斯基<ref name=yaroslavl>[http://school76.yar.ru/menu/work/virtualnew/zam_lyudi.htm Konstantin Ushinsky] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929125522/http://school76.yar.ru/menu/work/virtualnew/zam_lyudi.htm |date=2007-09-29 }} {{ru icon}} </ref>的家庭。不久他们移居到乌克兰诺夫哥罗德-谢维尔斯克城附近，他父亲在那里担任uyezd judge <ref name=teacher>[http://www.mifp.ru/pedagogika/Ibk/5/ushin.htm ''The teacher of Russian teachers''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070127162641/http://www.mifp.ru/pedagogika/Ibk/5/ushin.htm |date=2007-01-27 }} official site of [[Moscow_University_of_Industry_and_Finance|Moscow University of Industry and Finance]] </ref>。1840年，乌申斯基进入[[莫斯科大学|莫斯科大学]]法律系，1844年毕业<ref name=Brockhaus/><ref name=teacher/>。1846年-1849年担任[[雅罗斯拉夫尔|雅罗斯拉夫尔]]高等法政学校<!-- Demidov-->教授，但后来由于自由主义思想而被迫离开<ref name=bse/><ref name=teacher/>。

乌申斯基失业以后，依靠为杂志Sovremennik和Biblioteka dlya Chteniya写稿为生。一年半以后，乌申斯基在内务部宗教事务司找到一个科长助理的职位，虽然这个职业让他非常厌烦<ref name=teacher/>。 

1854年，乌申斯基成为加特钦斯克孤儿院的教师，1855年-1859年担任孤儿院学监<ref name=Brockhaus/>。在那里，他在2个已有20多年无人动过的书柜中发现了[[裴斯泰洛齐|裴斯泰洛齐]]<!-- kept the library of a [[Johann_Heinrich_Pestalozzi|Pestalozzi]]的学生E. Hugel. 这一发现 strongly influenced Ushinsky's interest  int 理论教育学<ref name=teacher/>. -->

<!-- In 1859-1862 Ushinsky is the Inspector of the [[Smolny|Smolny]] [[Institute_for_Noble_Maidens|Institute for Noble Maidens]] in Saint-Petersburg, In 1860-1862 he also worked as the Chief Editor of the magazine ''Journal of Department of Education'' (Zhurnal Ministerstava Narodnogo Obrazovanija) <ref name=bse/>. After the conflict with the Department of Education Ushinsky was forced to go abroad to study school organizations in [[Switzerland|Switzerland]], [[Germany|Germany]], [[France|France]], [[Belgium|Belgium]] and [[Italy|Italy]] (1862-1867). The position was precepted by many as a honorary exile<ref name=teacher/>. --> 

<!-- At the end of his life Ushinsky mostly acted as a writer and publicist. Together with [[Nikolay_Ivanovich_Pirogov|Pirogov]] he may be considered as an author of the [[Emancipation_reform_of_1861|Great liberal reforms of 1860s]]. Emancipated peasants needed schools, the schools needed teachers and textbooks. Ushinsky spent a lot of efforts arguing the best way to organize ''Teachers Seminaries. He also wrote children's text books for leaning reading ''Kid's world'' (Detskij mir) and ''Native Word'' (Rodnoye Slovo) <ref name=peoples> [http://www.peoples.ru/state/teacher/ushinskiy/ ''Konstantin Ushinsky''] on peoples.ru encyclopedia {{ru icon}} </ref>. More than 10 mln of Ushinsky's books including 187 editions of 他的著作《祖国语言》在[[十月革命|十月革命]]之前已经被 <ref name=teacher/>. -->

{{OldStyleDate|1871年|1月3日|1870年12月22日}}，康斯坦丁·乌申斯基在[[敖德萨|敖德萨]]去世，安葬在[[基辅|基辅]]<ref name=bse/>。

==著作==

<!-- The [[Magna_Opus|Magna Opus]] of Ushinsky was his theoretical work ''Human as a subject of education: Pedagogical Anthropology'' in three volumes started in 1867 <ref name=teacher/>. According to Ushinsky the subject of education is human so it is impossible to achieve results in education without using the results of "anthropological sciences": philosophy, political economy, history, literature, psychology, anatomy, physiology<ref name=bse/>. According to Ushinsky "Pedagogical experience without science is an equivalent to witchcraft in medicine" <ref name=teacher/>. Among Ushinsky's breaks through was the new "Analytic-Synthetic Phonetic Method" for learning reading and writing. The approach is still the main method used in Russian schools <ref name=bse/>. -->


